# Architecture & Structure

## Stack (Verified via Context7 — June 2026)

- **Next.js 16** (App Router, React Server Components, Server Actions)
- **TypeScript 5** — `strict: true`, path aliases via `tsconfig.json`
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — CSS-first config with `@theme` blocks, no `tailwind.config.ts`
- **Zod** — runtime validation for all API inputs and external data
- **React Query (TanStack Query v5)** — server state, caching, background refetching
- **Zustand** — lightweight client-only UI state (modals, selections, ephemeral state)
- **Prisma** — database ORM with typed queries

## Project Structure

```
src/
  app/
    (marketing)/          # Public: landing, pricing, docs
    (dashboard)/          # Auth-gated: analytics, routing, alerts, compliance
      layout.tsx          # Shared dashboard shell
    api/                  # Route handlers (POST/GET per resource)
  components/
    ui/                   # Primitive atoms: Button, Input, Card, Badge, Modal
    features/             # Domain composites: FxWidget, RoutingCard, AlertFeed
  lib/
    utils/                # Pure helper functions
    validators/           # Zod schemas (reusable across API + forms)
    constants/            # App-wide constants and config
  hooks/                  # Custom React hooks (use* naming)
  types/                  # Shared TypeScript interfaces, enums, DTOs
  services/               # External integrations: stablecoin SDK, FX API, compliance
  stores/                 # Zustand stores (one file per domain)
public/                   # Static assets
```

## React Server Components Rules

- **Default to Server Components.** Add `"use client"` only when the component requires browser APIs, state, or event handlers.
- Never fetch data inside Client Components — fetch in Server Components and pass as props.
- Data mutations use **Server Actions** (not client-side fetch calls to `/api`).
- Keep Server/Client boundary at the leaf level — don't push `"use client"` up the tree.
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` in every route segment.

## API Route Design

- All routes live under `src/app/api/[resource]/route.ts`.
- Validate every request body and query param with a Zod schema before processing.
- Return consistent shape: `{ data: T | null; error: string | null }`.
- Use correct HTTP status codes. Never `200` with an error payload.
- Log errors server-side; never leak stack traces to the client response.

## Security

- All secrets in environment variables only. `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix strictly for values safe to expose to browsers.
- Validate and sanitize **all** user inputs server-side, regardless of client-side validation.
- Rate-limit all public API routes (use middleware or edge config).
- Auth guards via **Next.js Middleware** on `(dashboard)` route group — never rely on UI-only guards.
- Never store sensitive values (private keys, API secrets) in client-accessible stores or `localStorage`.
- Use HTTPS-only cookies for session tokens (`httpOnly`, `secure`, `sameSite: strict`).

## Performance

- Use `next/image` for all images: always provide `width`, `height`, `alt`, and `priority` for above-fold images.
- Load fonts via `next/font` — never via CSS `@import` or `<link>` tags.
- Lazy-load heavy dashboard panels with `dynamic(() => import(...), { loading: () => <Skeleton /> })`.
- Prefer **streaming** with `Suspense` boundaries over blocking data fetches for dashboards.
- Avoid prop-drilling through 3+ layers — lift to context or Zustand store.
- Run `next build` and inspect bundle output before shipping features with new dependencies.

## Code Organization Principles

- Feature folder owns its components, hooks, and types — not scattered at root level.
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) per feature folder for clean imports.
- Services are pure functions or class instances — no React inside `services/`.
- Hooks encapsulate stateful logic only; business logic belongs in `lib/` or `services/`.
